history.content:
As courses, EECS 126 and 127 are mostly independent of each other.  They come together beautifully in CS 189.

EECS 126 and 188 will complement each other nicely.  Math 110 prior knowledge is a good way to get the most out of EECS 127.

-----------

I am very interested in AI/ML and I have already taken CS170, EE16a, and EE16b. I am deciding whether to take EECS126 or EE127 next semester with CS188, but I am not sure if there is a recommended order, or a suggested prerequisite to EECS127 such as Math 53. I know that Professor Sahai recommends taking EECS126 to supplement CS70, but does that mean 126 should be taken before 127? Is there any advantage to taking 126 before 127 or vice-versa? Which sequence will prepare students more for 189?

Also, if I take 127 first, will I have gaps in information that I should have learned in 126?
